# SIXMEN Frontend (HYBRID)

## Memory Scope

This rule must keep active:

- **Scope governed:** Filament vs Livewire, permission UI, Service delegation, UI ≠ security boundary.
- **Canonical context:** `docs/erp/core/05_Screen_Specs.md` · `docs/erp/ui/walkthrough/*` · `docs/erp/core/04_Architecture.md` §2 HYBRID · `docs/erp/phases/GD1_Kho_SX/09_Permission_Matrix.md`.
- **Required project memory:** ẩn nút ≠ authorize · mọi mutation → Policy → 403 · Livewire/Filament gọi Service, không business logic trong Blade.
- **Deprecated / rejected:** jQuery/DataTables default · logic nghiệp vụ trong view · coi UI visibility là authorization.
- **Applies to:** `app/Filament/**`, `resources/views/**`, `app/Livewire/**`.
- **Does not apply to:** pure backend API; docs-only.
- **Conflict handling:** envelope/backend rules win on mutation path; governance on permission matrix change.
- **Stop condition:** mutation không có backend Policy · permission matrix change chưa Human Owner.

## Purpose

Filament CRUD + Custom Livewire workflows; permission UX aligned with backend Policy.

## Use when

- Filament Resource, form, table
- Livewire workflow (BOM, picking, reconciliation)
- Admin UI permission visibility

## Stack

- Filament 3: CRUD, Tables, Forms, Shield
- Custom Livewire: workflow phức tạp

| Filament | Livewire |
|----------|----------|
| CRUD đơn giản | BOM, picking, barcode scan |
| Users, roles, master | Reconciliation, dashboard phức tạp |

## UI is not security boundary

- Hiding button ≠ authorization
- Every mutation → backend **Policy** → **403** if denied
- Livewire/Filament must call **Service** — no business logic in Blade/view

## Permission UI

```php
public static function canCreate(): bool
{
    return auth()->user()->can('core.users.create');
}

public function delete(int $id): void
{
    $model = Model::findOrFail($id);
    $this->authorize('delete', $model);
    // delegate to Service
}
```

## Guardrails

- No jQuery/DataTables as default stack
- No business logic in Blade
- No action without permission check (UI + backend)

